wlanpi-mcp (0.3.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Migrate UFW handling to a ufw application profile, matching the
    wlanpi-core pattern. The profile is staged at
    /etc/wlanpi-mcp/ufw/wlanpi-mcp.rules and installed into
    /etc/ufw/applications.d/wlanpi-mcp by a versioned setup script, which
    then runs 'ufw allow wlanpi-mcp' instead of a hardcoded '8766/tcp'.
    The port now lives in one declarative file and the resulting rule is
    named rather than a bare port literal.
  * postinst is now chroot-aware: on a live install it applies rules
    directly; during an image build (chroot, ufw inactive) it enables a
    wlanpi-mcp-ufw-first-boot.service oneshot to apply them on first boot.
    This fixes the ufw allow silently no-op'ing at image-build time.
  * The setup script drops any legacy literal 8766/tcp rule from pre-0.3.3
    packages so upgrades don't leave a duplicate in 'ufw status'.
  * postrm removes the (non-dpkg-owned) applications.d profile and the
    installed-rules-version marker, deleting the rule before the profile
    so ufw can still resolve the name.

 -- Jake Snyder <jsnyder81@gmail.com>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 18:41:32 +0000

wlanpi-mcp (0.3.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Stop suppressing ufw output in postinst/postrm: a field install
    silently ended up with only the IPv6 allow rule for 8766, leaving
    LAN MCP clients timing out. Rule add/delete results now appear in
    the apt/image-build log; '|| true' still prevents install aborts.
  * Sync wlanpi_mcp.__version__ with the package version (was left at
    0.3.0 in the 0.3.1 release).

 -- Jake Snyder <jsnyder81@gmail.com>  Thu, 16 Jul 2026 15:51:45 +0000

wlanpi-mcp (0.3.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Move default SSE port from 8765 to 8766: 8765 collides with the
    wlanpi-fpms2 state service, leaving whichever service started second
    in a crash loop. Updates config default, server fallback, shipped
    config.env template, install banner, and UFW open/close rules.

 -- Jake Snyder <jsnyder81@gmail.com>  Wed, 16 Jul 2026 05:00:00 -0600

wlanpi-mcp (0.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security: bind each SSE session to the token that opened it. The
    middleware publishes a per-token principal (sha256 fingerprint) so the
    MCP transport rejects any POST /messages/ presenting a different token,
    closing cross-session tool-call injection when a session id is known.
  * Tag outbound wlanpi-core calls with 'X-Wlanpi-Client: mcp' so core's
    nginx routes on-box (localhost) requests to the JWT validator instead of
    the localhost HMAC path (which needs a root-owned secret this
    unprivileged service cannot read). Requires the companion wlanpi-core
    nginx change; on-box JWT passthrough works without pointing
    WLANPI_CORE_URL at a LAN IP.
  * docs/auth-flow.md: document the end-to-end auth path and session binding.

 -- WLAN Pi Developers <developers@wlanpi.com>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

wlanpi-mcp (0.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Full endpoint coverage of wlanpi-core 2.1.11 API
  * New system tools: device model, service restart, datetime/timezone
    management, reboot/shutdown (gated by ALLOW_POWER_CONTROL, default on),
    hotspot client count and SSID/passphrase
  * New network diagnostics tools: routing table, TCP/UDP connections,
    DHCP leases, per-interface link stats, DHCP renew, WLAN USB/PCI
    drivers, public IPv6, ethernet interface details
  * New wifi tools: PHY capabilities, regulatory info, hotspot stations
    and per-station link stats
  * New utils tools: speedtest, ethernet port blinker start/stop/status
  * New bluetooth tool: discoverable pairing mode
  * Migrated Wi-Fi scan to canonical /api/v1/utils/wlan/scan endpoint
  * Removed tools backed by deprecated/removed wlan endpoints
    (connect_wlan, get_wlan_interfaces, get_connected_network) — use the
    network config tools instead
  * JWT bearer-token passthrough authentication for SSE transport
  * postinst: open UFW port 8765/tcp for SSE clients (closed on remove);
    default config now matches the JWT passthrough design (removes stale
    API-key/shared-secret settings)

 -- WLAN Pi Developers <developers@wlanpi.com>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

wlanpi-mcp (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release — Phase 1 MVP
  * Read tools: device info/stats, network interfaces, network info,
    service status, reachability, USB interfaces, UFW status
  * Write tools: service start/stop (allowlisted services only)
  * MCP resources: device://info, device://stats, network://interfaces,
    network://info, services://status/{name}
  * MCP prompts: diagnose_connectivity, troubleshoot_service,
    health_check, service_manager
  * Supports stdio and SSE transports

